Yes. You could say that.

541
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:07,100
Sensei, you did nothing wrong.

542
00:26:07,100 --> 00:26:10,090
I know they'll eventually understand.
Daichi-kun, too.

543
00:26:10,660 --> 00:26:13,870
No. It's my fault.

544
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:20,040
I told Sakagami-san that the children's feelings
are of utmost importance, and yet,

545
00:26:20,040 --> 00:26:23,190
they heard about the divorce
in the worst way possible.

546
00:26:23,190 --> 00:26:26,620
That's because the wife got
angry and left in a huff.

547
00:26:26,620 --> 00:26:28,680
I'm the one who made his wife angry.

548
00:26:30,240 --> 00:26:31,750
It was my mistake.

549
00:26:40,460 --> 00:26:43,080
Yes, Hakamada Law Office.

550
00:26:43,490 --> 00:26:44,910
Sakagami-san?

551
00:26:45,550 --> 00:26:46,830
What?

552
00:26:46,830 --> 00:26:48,740
Daichi-kun and the others?

553
00:26:50,430 --> 00:26:52,630
They left quite a long time ago.

554
00:26:53,900 --> 00:26:55,710
Hakamada
Law Office

555
00:27:00,780 --> 00:27:02,210
Hakamada-sensei.

556
00:27:03,220 --> 00:27:04,150
Sakagami-san.

557
00:27:04,150 --> 00:27:06,110
They're not at school or the playground.

558
00:27:06,110 --> 00:27:07,170
What about your sister's house?

559
00:27:07,170 --> 00:27:08,380
Not there, either.

560
00:27:08,380 --> 00:27:10,160
I bet it's my wife.

561
00:27:10,160 --> 00:27:11,320
My wife kidnapped them!

562
00:27:11,320 --> 00:27:13,760
Do you know where her new residence is?

563
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:16,460
I've got the address. Let's go.

564
00:27:16,460 --> 00:27:18,280
Sakagami-san.

565
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:20,330
The divorce is not yet final.

566
00:27:19,260 --> 00:27:30,140
If the divorce is not yet final

567
00:27:20,330 --> 00:27:24,480
She can't be charged for kidnapping.

568
00:27:22,130 --> 00:27:30,140
If the wife takes the children,
she cannot be charged with kidnapping.

569
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:26,160
Is that so?

570
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:30,590
Not only that, if your children's life
with your wife stabilizes,

571
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:33,660
there's a possibility that
your wife will get custody.

572
00:27:34,210 --> 00:27:36,110
That can't be...

573
00:27:36,110 --> 00:27:38,630
Please, give the children back!

574
00:27:38,630 --> 00:27:40,950
You're stubborn.
I told you, they're not here.

575
00:27:40,950 --> 00:27:41,580
You're lying.

576
00:27:41,580 --> 00:27:42,760
I'm not lying.

577
00:27:42,760 --> 00:27:45,490
If you don't believe me,
go look inside, everywhere.

578
00:27:47,090 --> 00:27:52,210
It's true that I approached them
and asked them to live with me.

579
00:27:52,210 --> 00:27:54,960
In front of that lawyer's office.

580
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:56,000
But...

581
00:27:57,370 --> 00:27:59,370
They wouldn't come with me.

582
00:28:00,160 --> 00:28:01,440
Really?

583
00:28:02,470 --> 00:28:04,000
Really.

584
00:28:04,500 --> 00:28:07,470
Then, where could they be?

585
00:28:07,470 --> 00:28:08,740
How would I know?

586
00:28:08,740 --> 00:28:10,880
It's your fault for neglecting them!

587
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:12,370
Don't make it my fault!

588
00:28:12,370 --> 00:28:13,800
It's all your fault!

589
00:28:13,800 --> 00:28:16,890
You'll be held responsible
if anything happens to them!

590
00:28:16,890 --> 00:28:18,580
This is no time for quarreling.

591
00:28:18,580 --> 00:28:20,160
Let's split up and look for them.

592
00:28:26,810 --> 00:28:28,180
Daichi-kun!

593
00:28:31,290 --> 00:28:32,730
Daichi-kun!

594
00:28:32,730 --> 00:28:34,550
Daichi-kun!

595
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:36,760
Yuna-chan!

596
00:28:40,180 --> 00:28:41,470
Sorata-kun!

597
00:28:41,470 --> 00:28:42,740
Daichi!

598
00:28:43,870 --> 00:28:45,140
Yuna!

599
00:28:47,460 --> 00:28:48,830
Sorata!

600
00:28:49,820 --> 00:28:52,420
Brother, I'm cold.

601
00:28:54,510 --> 00:28:55,970
Let's go home.

602
00:28:55,970 --> 00:28:58,330
No way. We're never going home.

603
00:28:58,330 --> 00:29:01,210
Where's the picnic place?

604
00:29:01,210 --> 00:29:03,590
We'll never get there.

605
00:29:04,570 --> 00:29:05,830
Brother.

606
00:29:10,070 --> 00:29:11,540
What's that?

607
00:29:11,540 --> 00:29:13,400
I'm scared.

608
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:14,510
Don't worry.

609
00:29:31,790 --> 00:29:34,190
Ghost!

610
00:29:34,190 --> 00:29:35,590
Who are you calling a ghost?!

611
00:29:38,790 --> 00:29:40,110
Hakamada-sensei,

612
00:29:40,110 --> 00:29:42,660
I've got the kids. They're safe.

613
00:29:42,660 --> 00:29:47,270
Thanks to Iron Spy Woman
Marilyn, season 15, episode 7.

614
00:29:44,070 --> 00:29:46,370
Iron Spy Woman
Marilyn

615
00:29:47,270 --> 00:29:49,750
Finding missing persons
is easy as pie.

616
00:29:49,750 --> 00:29:50,340
Because...

617
00:29:50,340 --> 00:29:55,800
99% of missing persons have left
a clue behind in their homes.

618
00:29:58,440 --> 00:30:01,480
Daichi, why did you do this?

619
00:30:02,970 --> 00:30:05,790
I won't know if you don't tell me.

620
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:11,830
I think Daichi-kun
yearned for this place,

621
00:30:11,830 --> 00:30:14,400
where he and his family went together.

622
00:30:16,350 --> 00:30:17,670
Is that so?

623
00:30:19,590 --> 00:30:20,840
Daichi.

624
00:30:22,110 --> 00:30:24,690
Please, don't give
your Papa a hard time.

625
00:30:26,850 --> 00:30:29,210
You're the one giving us a hard time.

626
00:30:30,020 --> 00:30:33,520
I want to live with Papa
and Mama. That's all!

627
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:37,250
Papa, you're stupid!

628
00:30:39,910 --> 00:30:40,460
Daichi-kun.

629
00:30:40,460 --> 00:30:41,290
Don't touch me!

630
00:30:42,790 --> 00:30:44,980
I hate you!

631
00:30:44,980 --> 00:30:46,030
Daichi.

632
00:30:46,030 --> 00:30:47,640
You liar!

633
00:30:48,950 --> 00:30:50,660
Mama told me about you.

634
00:30:50,660 --> 00:30:53,900
You're not a superhero of justice!

635
00:30:53,900 --> 00:30:58,010
You're a villain that's splitting
Mama and Papa apart!

636
00:31:02,280 --> 00:31:05,130
I'm not your friend anymore!

637
00:31:05,130 --> 00:31:07,840
Daichi, enough is enough!

638
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:09,860
Papa, Mama, and Mister,

639
00:31:09,860 --> 00:31:11,550
I hate you all!

640
00:31:21,400 --> 00:31:25,840
I don't believe you did
anything wrong, Sensei.

641
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:27,570
Huh?

642
00:31:27,570 --> 00:31:29,140
You're doing everything you can

643
00:31:29,140 --> 00:31:30,700
to the best of your ability,

644
00:31:30,700 --> 00:31:33,070
for the sake of
Sakagami-san and the kids.

645
00:31:33,070 --> 00:31:34,980
You've done nothing wrong.

646
00:31:35,490 --> 00:31:39,350
No, he's not entirely incorrect.

647
00:31:40,250 --> 00:31:42,420
From the perspective
of the children,

648
00:31:42,420 --> 00:31:44,180
I am a villain.

649
00:31:45,910 --> 00:31:51,270
Because I'm helping their beloved
Papa and Mama get a divorce.

650
00:31:53,420 --> 00:32:00,200
It's only natural that children
will want to live as a family.

651
00:32:01,390 --> 00:32:05,240
I always felt that way
when I was a child, too.

652
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:09,890
But, it was the wife's illicit activities

653
00:32:09,890 --> 00:32:12,150
that broke the family apart.

654
00:32:12,150 --> 00:32:14,020
She doesn't participate in household duties,
or caring for her children.

655
00:32:14,020 --> 00:32:16,620
Instead she's out committing adultery.

656
00:32:16,620 --> 00:32:18,680
How can the children be happy
living with a mother like that?

657
00:32:20,210 --> 00:32:25,020
Regardless, she's their
one and only mother.

658
00:32:27,260 --> 00:32:29,510
They want to live together as a family.

659
00:32:31,560 --> 00:32:35,430
Lawyers are powerless
at a time like this.

660
00:32:51,900 --> 00:32:55,150
Sensei is so gloomy lately.

661
00:32:55,150 --> 00:32:57,020
Tomorrow is the conciliation.

662
00:32:57,020 --> 00:32:59,620
I wonder if he's ready for it.

663
00:33:00,470 --> 00:33:02,070
The children running away

664
00:33:02,070 --> 00:33:04,260
might reverberate loudly
at conciliation court.

665
00:33:04,260 --> 00:33:08,030
And if that happens,
the mother will get custody.

666
00:33:08,030 --> 00:33:10,440
If that happens,

667
00:33:10,440 --> 00:33:14,340
how will he pay the three
months worth of rent?

668
00:33:15,200 --> 00:33:18,670
Court of Law

669
00:33:16,430 --> 00:33:20,160
We will now commence the
conciliation hearing.

670
00:33:18,670 --> 00:33:22,610
Family Court: Conciliation Room

671
00:33:20,160 --> 00:33:22,750
Both parties have their
respective attorneys.

672
00:33:22,750 --> 00:33:26,050
Both parties have wished for them
to be present at the discussion.

673
00:33:26,050 --> 00:33:28,590
Hence, we have arranged
the session accordingly.

674
00:33:28,590 --> 00:33:30,810
According to the family conciliator,

675
00:33:30,810 --> 00:33:34,850
it would be appropriate for the mother,
Izumi-san, to get custody of her children.

676
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:37,930
Izumi's lawyer:
Shoji Akiko

677
00:33:34,850 --> 00:33:35,930
The other day,

678
00:33:35,930 --> 00:33:39,650
there was an incident wherein
the children ran away from home.

679
00:33:39,650 --> 00:33:43,210
The children were under
Takeshi-san's supervision at the time.

680
00:33:43,210 --> 00:33:45,870
If Takeshi-san were to get custody,

681
00:33:45,870 --> 00:33:48,890
something like that could
very well happen again.

682
00:33:48,890 --> 00:33:52,810
I cannot rely on a person like that
to watch over my children.

683
00:33:52,810 --> 00:33:55,310
And with regard to the
financial situation...

684
00:33:55,310 --> 00:33:58,920
pardon me for asking, but Takeshi-san,
what is your annual income?

685
00:33:59,340 --> 00:34:02,070
I plan for it to be around
three and a half million yen.

686
00:34:02,070 --> 00:34:04,620
You recently found a job, correct?

687
00:34:04,620 --> 00:34:05,500
Yes.

688
00:34:05,500 --> 00:34:07,490
At an electrical engineering company.

689
00:34:07,490 --> 00:34:10,320
I will work hard and get promoted.

690
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:12,150
Or get fired, again.

691
00:34:13,660 --> 00:34:16,230
Izumi-san's annual income
is six million yen.

692
00:34:16,230 --> 00:34:19,260
The partner she would remarry
earns 12 million yen.

693
00:34:19,260 --> 00:34:21,910
That makes a total of 18 million yen.

694
00:34:22,390 --> 00:34:25,240
In terms of affording a good
education for the children...

695
00:34:25,240 --> 00:34:26,970
they are nowhere lacking.

696
00:34:28,680 --> 00:34:31,270
Sensei, are you all right?

697
00:34:32,030 --> 00:34:33,650
If I may.

698
00:34:33,650 --> 00:34:34,340
Please.

699
00:34:35,020 --> 00:34:37,200
Firstly, concerning
the runaway incident.

700
00:34:37,200 --> 00:34:40,990
Izumi-san is the cause of
the children running away.

701
00:34:40,990 --> 00:34:43,930
Izumi-san revealed the
plan to divorce to them,

702
00:34:43,930 --> 00:34:46,510
and thereby hurt her
children's feelings deeply.

703
00:34:46,510 --> 00:34:47,930
What's that supposed to mean?

704
00:34:47,930 --> 00:34:51,900
The most careful one must
be when divorcing...

705
00:34:51,900 --> 00:34:54,870
is when that fact is
revealed to children.

706
00:34:55,290 --> 00:34:57,240
But Izumi-san lost
control of her emotions.

707
00:34:57,240 --> 00:34:59,100
She disparaged Takeshi-san
in front of them,

708
00:34:59,630 --> 00:35:02,010
and deeply hurt her children's feelings.

709
00:35:02,010 --> 00:35:04,120
Let's not stay here
with this no-good Papa.

710
00:35:04,120 --> 00:35:06,980
Let's live in a new house,
with a new Papa.

711
00:35:06,980 --> 00:35:09,040
She could very well have
such outbursts again,

712
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:10,540
neglecting her children's feelings.

713
00:35:10,540 --> 00:35:12,720
I merely spoke the truth.

714
00:35:12,720 --> 00:35:14,790
There's no point in lying to them.

715
00:35:15,590 --> 00:35:19,610
Next, with regard to the
financial situation.

716
00:35:19,610 --> 00:35:21,780
Indeed, Izumi-san's new partner

717
00:35:21,780 --> 00:35:24,500
is the president of an associate
company, isn't that so?

718
00:35:25,620 --> 00:35:28,190
Have you changed your
mind about marrying him?

719
00:35:28,190 --> 00:35:29,900
I have not.

720
00:35:29,900 --> 00:35:31,420
I see.

721
00:35:31,420 --> 00:35:33,300
We have a problem, then.

722
00:35:33,680 --> 00:35:37,280
His annual income may
very well be 12 million yen.

723
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:41,280
But his company is in debt
far beyond that amount.

724
00:35:42,050 --> 00:35:42,850
What?

725
00:35:42,850 --> 00:35:45,520
They've been in the red
for several years now.

726
00:35:45,520 --> 00:35:47,350
They have been delinquent with taxes.

727
00:35:46,350 --> 00:35:47,350
Federal Income Tax Delinquency:
Foreclosure Warning

728
00:35:47,350 --> 00:35:48,790
They have unpaid salaries.

729
00:35:47,490 --> 00:35:48,790
Bill for Unpaid Wages

730
00:35:48,790 --> 00:35:50,960
They have been delinquent
in paying back loans.

731
00:35:48,950 --> 00:35:50,960
Final Notice

732
00:35:50,960 --> 00:35:54,310
Thus, their bankruptcy
is only a matter of time.

733
00:35:54,310 --> 00:35:55,290
That can't be.

734
00:35:55,290 --> 00:35:58,800
Eventually, Izumi-san's income

735
00:35:58,800 --> 00:36:01,630
will be redirected to paying back their debts.

736
00:36:02,530 --> 00:36:06,940
You had said you would hire a babysitter
to look after your children.

737
00:36:06,940 --> 00:36:08,890
That is looking rather difficult now.

738
00:36:08,890 --> 00:36:12,580
How will you pay your attorney fees?

739
00:36:13,210 --> 00:36:14,210
Also,

740
00:36:14,210 --> 00:36:17,370
your partner has a child
from his previous marriage.

741
00:36:17,370 --> 00:36:19,260
His ex-wife has custody of the child.

742
00:36:20,060 --> 00:36:22,420
Do you know why he gave her custody?

743
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:26,490
Because he knows it's better
for the mother to have custody.

744
00:36:26,490 --> 00:36:27,980
Wrong.

745
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:31,010
It appears he doesn't
like his child much.

746
00:36:31,730 --> 00:36:36,060
His violent actions toward his ex-wife and child
were the cause of their divorce.

747
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:38,160
The police became involved
on multiple occasions.

748
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:45,310
Will your children

749
00:36:45,310 --> 00:36:47,710
be happy living with a person like that?

750
00:37:02,200 --> 00:37:05,130
I will now express my
opinion as conciliator.

751
00:37:08,740 --> 00:37:11,030
Gauging the overall situation,

752
00:37:11,030 --> 00:37:13,500
the custody of all three children

753
00:37:14,390 --> 00:37:17,590
should go to the father, Takeshi-san.

754
00:37:17,590 --> 00:37:19,380
Izumi-san, is this agreeable?

755
00:37:20,170 --> 00:37:21,860
I cannot accept that.

756
00:37:21,860 --> 00:37:23,870
If you cannot accept it,

757
00:37:23,870 --> 00:37:25,550
we can dismiss the
conciliation as undetermined,

758
00:37:25,550 --> 00:37:28,650
and you can take it to court to
have a judge make the decision.

759
00:37:29,360 --> 00:37:30,620
You can appeal it,

760
00:37:30,620 --> 00:37:33,930
but I doubt you'd get custody.

761
00:37:37,410 --> 00:37:40,060
It appears both parties
are in agreement.

762
00:37:40,060 --> 00:37:42,450
I now declare the
conciliation as determinedâ€”

763
00:37:42,450 --> 00:37:43,460
One moment please.

764
00:37:44,190 --> 00:37:45,300
What is it?

765
00:37:46,100 --> 00:37:47,770
I am sorry to say,

766
00:37:47,770 --> 00:37:52,580
but I think both Sakagami-san and
Izumi-san are unfit to take on custody.

767
00:37:53,050 --> 00:37:54,540
Hakamada-sensei.

768
00:37:58,180 --> 00:38:00,990
If the two of you really
care about your children,

769
00:38:01,460 --> 00:38:04,880
why did you destroy their happiness?

770
00:38:10,900 --> 00:38:17,020
All you were concerned about
was who would win custody.

771
00:38:18,430 --> 00:38:20,950
Children are not your possessions.

772
00:38:23,470 --> 00:38:25,850
The children are innocent.

773
00:38:27,380 --> 00:38:29,710
Children always end up the victims.

774
00:38:30,590 --> 00:38:33,050
If you truly care about your children,

775
00:38:34,020 --> 00:38:37,030
then you must first ask their forgiveness,
for having destroyed their happiness.

776
00:38:43,680 --> 00:38:45,990
You need to keep your heads bowed,

777
00:38:46,810 --> 00:38:48,530
until their wounds are healed.

778
00:38:56,910 --> 00:38:58,800
And you must wish for their happiness,

779
00:38:59,650 --> 00:39:01,980
from the bottom of your heart.

780
00:39:07,830 --> 00:39:11,910
Isn't that where their happiness begins?

781
00:39:24,910 --> 00:39:26,250
You.

782
00:39:26,940 --> 00:39:29,250
You're a lawyer.
What do you know?

783
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:31,170
This is ridiculous.

784
00:39:48,750 --> 00:39:52,380
We're going to be living
apart from Mama.

785
00:39:53,010 --> 00:39:54,460
It's Papa's fault.

786
00:39:55,160 --> 00:39:58,490
This time it really is.

787
00:39:58,490 --> 00:40:02,590
No! I don't want to
live apart from Mama!

788
00:40:02,590 --> 00:40:05,130
Why is Mama going away?

789
00:40:05,130 --> 00:40:08,140
I want Mama to live with us!

790
00:40:11,360 --> 00:40:12,440
I'm sorry.

791
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:25,450
Hakamada
Law Office

792
00:40:25,450 --> 00:40:28,090
I'm so glad for Sakagami-san.

793
00:40:28,090 --> 00:40:29,720
He got custody and child support.

794
00:40:29,720 --> 00:40:33,240
But why did he withdraw
the compensation fee?

795
00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:37,680
He must've taken Izumi-san's
future into consideration.

796
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:39,410
He's a pushover.

797
00:40:39,410 --> 00:40:42,410
If it were me, I'd mercilessly
collect what I could.

798
00:40:42,410 --> 00:40:44,900
I'd chase them down to the pits of Hell!

799
00:40:44,900 --> 00:40:46,810
Me too, to the pits of Hell.

800
00:40:46,810 --> 00:40:48,900
Oh! Rent comes first.

801
00:40:48,900 --> 00:40:50,540
